The paper deals with distributed protocols in the partial synchrony setting with Byzantine nodes, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses state-machine replication, which is a topic in Distributed Systems (cs.DS). The problem of Byzantine View Synchronization is related to fault tolerance and security, which are topics in Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses communication complexity, which is a topic in Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
